21#ifndef GCC_GCSE_H
22#define GCC_GCSE_H
23
24/* Target-dependent globals. */
25struct target_gcse {
26 /* Nonzero for each mode that supports (set (reg) (reg)).
27 This is trivially true for integer and floating point values.
28 It may or may not be true for condition codes. */
29 char x_can_copy[(int) NUM_MACHINE_MODES];
30
31 /* True if the previous field has been initialized. */
32 bool x_can_copy_init_p;
33};
34
35extern struct target_gcse default_target_gcse;
36#if SWITCHABLE_TARGET
37extern struct target_gcse *this_target_gcse;
38#else
39#define this_target_gcse (&default_target_gcse)
40#endif
41
42void gcse_c_finalize (void);
43extern bool gcse_or_cprop_is_too_expensive (const char *);
44
45#endif
